.TH LUNIS 1 "2026-06-25" "Lunis CLI" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lunis \- East Asian lunisolar calendar CLI

.SH DESCRIPTION
Converts a Gregorian date to the Chinese/Vietnamese/Japanese/Korean lunisolar calendar.
Computes the sexagenary cycle (stems, branches, yinyang, wuxing) for year, month, day,
and hour pillars. Supports TenGod (十神) relationships, NaYin (纳音) attributes,
hidden stems (藏干), and day auspiciousness scoring.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
convert
Reads a date from standard input in \fBRFC 3339\fP format, e.g., `2026-03-02T23:40:33+07:00`.
You can pipe input like:

.nf
$ date -Iseconds | lunis convert -l vi -f "{y-s} {y-b} - {m-s} {m-b} ({m-S}) - {d-s} {d-b} | Giờ {h-b} - {ke} khắc"
.fi

.TP
now
Uses the \fBcurrent system time\fP as input. For example:

.nf
$ lunis now -l zh -f "{y-s} {y-b} - {m-S} - {d-s} {d-b} | Giờ {h-b} - {ke}"
.fi

.TP
relation
Check the TenGod (十神) interaction between two dates.

.nf
$ lunis relation -l vi "2000-01-01T12:00:00+07:00" "2026-03-02T00:59:33+07:00"
.fi

.TP
judge
Judge whether a day is auspicious based on your birth date.

.nf
$ lunis judge -l vi -b "2000-01-01T12:00:00+07:00"
.fi

.SH USAGE
lunis <command> [OPTIONS]

.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
-l, --lang <LANG>
Language for output: vi, zh, ko, jp
.TP
-f, --format <FORMAT>
Format string for output (see FORMAT STRING below)
.TP
-o, --output <MODE>
Output mode: \fBdefault\fP (plain text) or \fBwaybar\fP (JSON for Waybar)
.TP
\-\-tooltip-format <FORMAT>
Separate format string for the Waybar tooltip field

.SH RELATION OPTIONS
.TP
-p, --pillar <PILLAR>
Target pillar: year, month, day (default), hour
.TP
-a, --all
Show all four pillars with hidden stems (overrides \fB--pillar\fP)
.TP
\-\-nayin
Show NaYin (纳音) attribute for the target date

.SH JUDGE OPTIONS
.TP
-b, --born <RFC3339>
(Required) Birth date in RFC 3339 format
.TP
-t, --target <RFC3339>
Target date to evaluate (defaults to current time)

.SH TIMEZONE HANDLING
The tool \fBignores the timezone\fP. All calculations are based solely on the
provided datetime values, without conversion between zones.

.SH FORMAT STRING
Your format string supports placeholders:

.TP
\{y-s\} / \{y-b\} / \{y-y\} / \{y-w\} / \{y-n\}
Year: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number

.TP
\{m-s\} / \{m-b\} / \{m-y\} / \{m-w\} / \{m-n\} / \{m-S\}
Month: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number, localized string
(e.g., "Tháng Giêng", "正月", "闰三月")

.TP
\{d-s\} / \{d-b\} / \{d-y\} / \{d-w\} / \{d-n\}
Day: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number

.TP
\{h-s\} / \{h-b\} / \{h-y\} / \{h-w\} / \{h-n\}
Hour: stem, branch, yinyang, wuxing, number (0–23)

.TP
\{ke\}
15-minute ke division (0–7)

.SH EXAMPLES
Convert a date with Vietnamese output:

.nf
$ echo "2026-03-02T23:40:33+07:00" | lunis convert -l vi -f "{y-s} {y-b} - {m-s} {m-b} ({m-S}) - {d-s} {d-b} | Giờ {h-b} - {ke} khắc"
Bính Ngọ - Canh Dần (Tháng Giêng) - Ất Hợi | Giờ Tý - 2 khắc
.fi

Check TenGod relation in Chinese:

.nf
$ lunis relation -l zh "2000-01-01T12:00:00+07:00" "2026-03-02T00:59:33+07:00"
.fi

Show all four pillars with hidden stems:

.nf
$ lunis relation --all -l vi "2000-01-01T12:00:00+07:00" "2026-03-02T00:59:33+07:00"
.fi

Show NaYin attribute:

.nf
$ lunis relation --nayin -l zh "2000-01-01T12:00:00+07:00" "2026-03-02T00:59:33+07:00"
.fi

Judge day auspiciousness:

.nf
$ lunis judge -l vi -b "2000-01-01T12:00:00+07:00"
.fi

Waybar JSON output:

.nf
$ lunis now -o waybar -l vi
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
date(1), cal(1)

